The paper deals with a computer vision problem of spectral super-resolution using deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a new class of modules called function-mixture blocks, which are used to determine the receptive field size and mapping function pixel-wise. This involves learning a complicated mapping function using a deep convolutional neural network, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of linear mixing and feature fusion, which are techniques used in neural networks and fall under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
